<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-688-526  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 688 526.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MacWEEK  July 31 1990 v4 n26 p30(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Coastal Associates Publishing L.P. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Sigma offers low-emission displays. (Sigma Designs Inc. offerslow-emission monitors)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Webster, John.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Sigma Designs Inc. (marketing).andO;Ticker:    SIGM.andO;Product:   Sigma Designs L-View (Monitor, monochrome) (marketing)Sigma Designs PageView (Monitor, monochrome) (marketing)Sigma Designs SilverView (Monitor, monochrome) (marketing).andO;Topic:     Market EntryMonitorsOccupational HealthRadiationMonochrome.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>By John WebsterandM;Fremont, Calif.andP;  -- In the wake of the VDT emissions turbulence swirlingthroughout the computer industry, Sigma Designs Inc. last week announced thatit has begun U.S.andP;  sales of low-emissions versions of its gray-scale andmonochrome monitors that were available only in Sweden.andM;The Swedish-edition 15-inch PageView, 19-inch L-View and 21-inch SilverViewmonitors comply with the Swedish government's standards for very lowfrequency (VLF) emissions, which are more stringent than U.S.andP;  standards.andM;The standard U.S.andP;  models cost from $1,499 to $2,199; the versions designedto Swedish specifications sell for an additional $200 each.andM;Sigma hopes to attract users who are nervous about the reported effects ofmagnetic field emissions, including VLF and extremely low frequency (ELF)radiation.andM;While ELF emissions have dominated discussions of the problem sparked by arecent article in Macworld magazine, Sigma officials said other studiessuggest a link between the VLF portion of the electromagnetic spectrum andmedical troubles in pregnant women.andM;To reduce emissions, Sigma has &quot;put [into the monitor] additional circuitrythat produces a magnetic field equal and opposite to that being generated bythe monitor,&quot; said Charles Waters, Sigma director of marketing.andM;The company also announced last week that it is developing versions of thedisplays that will meet new standards for ELF emissions that the Swedishgovernment is expected to set next year.andP;  The displays will be available inthe United States and Sweden early next year.andM;Sigma Designs Inc. is located at 46501 Landing Parkway, Fremont, Calif.andO;94538; (415) 770-0100.andO;</TEXT></DOC>